This is the program 'finance_analysis'.

/* Calculate compound interest over time */
Create 'principal' as a double with value 10000.0.
Create 'rate' as a double with value 0.05.
Create 'years' as an int with value 10.
Create 'balance' as a double with value 'principal'.

For every iteration of 'y' from 1 through 'years':
    Replace 'balance' with 'balance' multiplied by the quantity 1.0 plus 'rate'.
    Call 'printf' with "Year %d: Balance = %.2f\n", 'y', and 'balance' stored to nothing.
End iteration of 'y' from 1 through 'years'.

/* String concatenation for report */
Create 'report_msg' as a string.
Call 'join' with "Final Balance: " and "PROCESSED" stored to 'report_msg'.
Call 'printf' with "%s\n", 'report_msg' stored to nothing.

End of the program 'finance_analysis'.
